The paper deals with signal processing and image super-resolution, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The use of linear systems and the analysis of quantitative error suggest that cs.IT (Information Theory) is a likely sub-category. The application of the proposed interpolation to image super-resolution and the comparison with state-of-the-art methods suggest that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. The use of simulations and experimental studies suggest that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are possible sub-categories. Finally, the use of the FFT technique and the fast algorithm suggest that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible sub-category as well.
